'''Bradley Clarke Zimmer''' (born November 27, 1992) is an American [[professional baseball]] [[center fielder]] for the [[Cleveland Indians]] of [[Major League Baseball]] (MLB). He attended the [[University of San Francisco]], and played [[college baseball]] for the [[San Francisco Dons baseball]] team. He was drafted by the Indians in the first round of the [[2014 Major League Baseball draft|2014 MLB draft]], and he made his MLB debut in 2017.

==Amateur career==
Zimmer attended [[La Jolla High School]] in [[San Diego|San Diego, California]], where he played for the school's baseball team.<ref name=lajolla>{{cite web |url=http://www.lajollalight.com/2011/05/04/draft-may-keep-la-jollas-zimmer-brothers-from-reunitin/ |title=Draft may keep La Jolla's Zimmer brothers from reuniting |publisher=La Jolla Light |date= |accessdate=June 3, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502004907/http://www.lajollalight.com/2011/05/04/draft-may-keep-la-jollas-zimmer-brothers-from-reunitin/ |archivedate=May 2, 2014  }}</ref><ref name=utsd/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sdnews.com/view/full_story/2542668/article-Zimmer-brothers-lead-Vikings-past-Torreys?instance=update1 |title=San Diego Community News Group – Zimmer brothers lead Vikings past Torreys |publisher=Sdnews.com |date=May 12, 2009 |accessdate=June 3, 2014}}</ref> The [[Chicago Cubs]] selected Zimmer in the 23rd round, with the 699th overall selection, of the [[2011 Major League Baseball draft|2011 Major League Baseball (MLB) Draft]], but Zimmer did not sign with the Cubs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chicago.cubs.mlb.com/team/draft.jsp?c_id=chc&year=2011 |title=Chicago Cubs 2011 Draft Results &#124; cubs.com: Team |publisher=MLB.com |date= |accessdate=June 3, 2014}}</ref>

[[File:Bradley_Zimmer_(5)_(6875178922).jpg|left|upright|thumb|Zimmer with the [[San Francisco Dons baseball|San Francisco Dons]]]]
Zimmer enrolled at the [[University of San Francisco]] (USF) to play [[college baseball]] for the [[San Francisco Dons baseball]] team. In 2014, his junior year, he was named a preseason [[All-America]]n<ref>{{cite web|author=Steve Kroner |url=http://www.sfgate.com/collegesports/article/Bay-Area-college-baseball-teams-ready-for-season-5222650.php |title=Bay Area college baseball teams ready for season |publisher=SFGate |date=February 11, 2014 |accessdate=June 3, 2014}}</ref> and to the [[Golden Spikes Award]]'s midseason watch list.<ref name=utsd>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.utsandiego.com/news/2014/Apr/14/carlsbad-la-jolla-cathedral-college-baseball-award/ |title=Three locals up for Golden Spikes Award |work=U-T San Diego |date=April 14, 2014 |accessdate=June 3, 2014}}</ref> He was considered to be among the best available [[prospect (sports)|prospects]] in the [[2014 Major League Baseball draft|2014 MLB draft]].<ref name=mlb/>  He finished his junior year at USF with a .368 [[batting average (baseball)|batting average]], seven [[home run]]s, 31 [[Run batted in|runs batted in]] (RBIs), and 21 [[stolen base]]s.<ref name=draft/>

==Professional career==
The [[Cleveland Indians]] selected Zimmer in the first round, 21st overall, of the [[2014 Major League Baseball draft]].<ref name=draft>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2014/06/cleveland_indians_take_univers.html |title=Cleveland Indians take University of San Francisco OF Bradley Zimmer with first pick |work=[[Cleveland Plain Dealer]] |date=June 5, 2014 |accessdate=June 8, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mercurynews.com/sports/ci_25908358/mlb-draft-usfs-bradley-zimmer-selected-no-21 |title=MLB Draft: USF's Bradley Zimmer selected No. 21 overall by Cleveland Indians – San Jose Mercury News |publisher=Mercurynews.com |date=June 5, 2014 |accessdate=June 8, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.morningjournal.com/sports/20140605/cleveland-indians-draft-outfielder-bradley-zimmer-pitcher-justus-sheffield-in-first-round-of-baseball-draft |title=Cleveland Indians draft outfielder Bradley Zimmer, pitcher Justus Sheffield in first round of baseball draft |publisher=Morningjournal.com |date=June 5, 2014 |accessdate=June 8, 2014}}</ref> He signed for a $1.9 million bonus on June 17, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/cle/cleveland-indians-sign-first-round-draft-pick-bradley-zimmer?ymd=20140617&content_id=80207220&vkey=news_cle|title=Indians sign first-round pick Zimmer|work=MLB.com|date=June 17, 2014|accessdate=February 17, 2015}}</ref> He then joined the [[Mahoning Valley Scrappers]] of the [[Class A-Short Season]] [[New York–Penn League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.morningjournal.com/sports/20140620/tribes-top-pick-zimmer-latest-to-join-mahoning-valley-scrappers|title=Tribe's top pick Zimmer latest to join Mahoning Valley Scrappers|work=morningjournal.com|accessdate=February 17, 2015}}</ref> He finished the season with the [[Lake County Captains]] of the [[Class A (baseball)|Class A]] [[Midwest League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2014/09/indians_first-round_pick_bradl.html|title=Indians first-round pick Bradley Zimmer adds depth to Lake County Captains championship quest|work=Cleveland Plain Dealer|accessdate=June 26, 2015}}</ref> In 2015, the Indians assigned Zimmer to the [[Lynchburg Hillcats]] of the [[Class A-Advanced]] [[Carolina League]]. He batted .305 with ten home runs and 32 stolen bases in 37 attempts in 77 games for Lynchburg.<ref name=akron/> Zimmer was selected to represent the Indians at the 2015 [[All-Star Futures Game]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.indians.mlb.com/news/article/132853704/indians-bradley-zimmer-in-futures-game|title=Tribe's Zimmer selected for Futures Game|work=MLB.com|accessdate=June 26, 2015}}</ref> Following the Futures Game, the Indians promoted Zimmer to the [[Akron RubberDucks]] of the [[Class AA (baseball)|Class AA]] [[Eastern League (baseball)|Eastern League]].<ref name=akron>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2015/07/cleveland_indians_promote_pros.html|title=Cleveland Indians promote prospect Bradley Zimmer to Class AA Akron|first=Paul|last=Hoynes|work=Cleveland Plain Dealer|date=July 14, 2015|accessdate=July 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.milb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20150718&content_id=137304692&fext=.jsp&vkey=news_milb&sid=milb|title=RubberDucks' Zimmer off to stellar start: Indians prospect gets three hits, three RBIs in third Double-A game|first=Robert|last=Emrich|work=MiLB.com|date=July 19, 2015|accessdate=July 19, 2015}}</ref> Zimmer batted .219 with Akron.<ref name=hairline/> The Indians assigned Zimmer to the [[Scottsdale Scorpions]] of the [[Arizona Fall League]] (AFL),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news-herald.com/sports/20150923/clint-frazier-and-bradley-zimmer-part-of-what-could-be-in-cleveland-indians-fall-development-program|title=Clint Frazier and Bradley Zimmer part of what could be in Cleveland Indians Fall Development program|work=[[The News-Herald (Ohio)|The News-Herald]]|first=Justin|last=Lada|date=September 23, 2015|accessdate=September 24, 2015}}</ref> but he was diagnosed with a hairline fracture in his right foot and considered unlikely to play in the AFL.<ref name=hairline>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2015/09/cleveland_indians_prospect_bra.html|title=Cleveland Indians prospect Bradley Zimmer dealing with broken bone in foot|work=cleveland.com|first= Zack|last=Meisel|date=September 23, 2015|accessdate=September 24, 2015}}</ref>

Zimmer began the 2016 season with Akron, and was promoted to the [[Columbus Clippers]] of the [[Class AAA]] [[International League]] on July 25.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2016/07/cleveland_indians_promote_top.html|title=Cleveland Indians promote top prospects Bradley Zimmer, Clint Frazier to Triple-A Columbus|work=Cleveland Plain Dealer|first=Zack|last=Meisel|date=July 24, 2016|accessdate=July 26, 2016}}</ref> Zimmer ended 2016 with a .250 [[batting average (baseball)|batting average]], 15 home runs and 62 RBIs, along with 38 stolen bases.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.milb.com/player/index.jsp?player_id=605548#/career/R/hitting/2016/ALL |title=Bradley Zimmer Stats, Highlights, Bio &#124; MiLB.com Stats &#124; The Official Site of Minor League Baseball |publisher=Milb.com |date= |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> After the season, the Indians assigned Zimmer to the Mesa Solar Sox of the [[Arizona Fall League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azcentral.com/story/news/local/mesa-contributor/2016/10/26/cubs-indians-prospects-mesa-solar-sox-teammates-arizona-fall-league/92792592/ |title=Cubs, Indians prospects are Mesa Solar Sox teammates in Arizona Fall League |publisher=Azcentral.com |date=October 26, 2016 |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> He returned to Columbus to start the 2017 season.<ref name=promote/>

The Indians promoted Zimmer to the major leagues on May 16, 2017.<ref name=promote>{{cite web|url=http://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2017/05/indians_bradley_zimmer_shawn_a.html |title=Cleveland Indians promote former 1st-round pick Bradley Zimmer to big-league roster |publisher=cleveland.com |date= |accessdate=May 16, 2017}}</ref> He made his MLB debut that day. In his second MLB game, on May 17, Zimmer recorded his first MLB hit and home run.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.morningjournal.com/sports/20170517/bradley-zimmer-hits-first-career-home-run-in-cleveland-indians-loss-7-4-to-rays |title=Bradley Zimmer hits first career home run in Cleveland Indians loss 7–4 to Rays |publisher=Morningjournal.com |date=May 17, 2017 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> On July 25, Zimmer hit his first [[grand slam (baseball)|grand slam]] against the [[Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim]], as the Indians won the game 11–7.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kosileski |first=William |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/indians-bradley-zimmer-hits-first-grand-slam/c-244403414 |title=Indians Bradley Zimmer hits first grand slam |publisher=MLB.com |date=May 24, 2018 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> Zimmer batted .241 with eight home runs and 39 RBIs in 299 [[at bat]]s for Cleveland.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hoynes |first=Paul |url=https://www.cleveland.com/expo/erry-2018/03/38eddee3b7/is_bradley_zimmer_destined_to.html |title=Is Bradley Zimmer destined to be a .200 hitter for the Cleveland Indians? Hey, Hoynsie! |publisher=cleveland.com |date=March 31, 2018 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref>

Zimmer began 2018 as Cleveland's starting [[center fielder]]. However, after batting .226 with a 42% strikeout rate in early June, he was [[option (baseball)|optioned]] to Triple-A Columbus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2018/06/cleveland_indians_activate_lon_1.html |title=Cleveland Indians activate Lonnie Chisenhall, option Bradley Zimmer to Class AAA Columbus |publisher=cleveland.com |date=June 5, 2018 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> After playing in eight games for Columbus, Zimmer injured his right shoulder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2018/06/bradley_zimmer_injures_right_s.html |title=Cleveland Indians' Bradley Zimmer injures right shoulder during batting drills in minors |publisher=cleveland.com |date=June 13, 2018 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> He had an [[anti-inflammatory]] shot and was shut down for four-to-six weeks in late June.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cleveland.com/tribe/index.ssf/2018/06/cleveland_indians_bradley_zimm_10.html |title=Cleveland Indians' Bradley Zimmer shut down for four to six weeks with sore right shoulder |publisher=cleveland.com |date=June 22, 2018 |accessdate=July 9, 2018}}</ref> On July 21, 2018, Zimmer underwent right shoulder surgery to repair a torn labrum, and was out for the rest of the year. Recovery time required 8-12 months.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bradley Zimmer has surgery, to return in 8-12 months |url=https://www.mlb.com/news/bradley-zimmer-has-surgery-on-right-shoulder/c-286715932 |publisher=MLB |accessdate=July 21, 2018}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Zimmer's father, Eric, played [[college baseball]] at the [[University of California, San Diego]]. He is an [[anesthesiologist]]. His mother, Cathy, ran track at [[San Diego State University]], and works as a counselor at La Jolla High.<ref name=lajolla/> His older brother, [[Kyle Zimmer|Kyle]], is a [[professional baseball]] [[pitcher]] in the [[Kansas City Royals]] organization.<ref name=mlb>{{cite web|url=http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article/mlb/promising-outfielder-bradley-zimmer-aims-to-follow-in-brothers-footsteps?ymd=20140522&content_id=76427950&vkey=news_mlb |title=Promising outfielder Bradley Zimmer aims to follow in brother's footsteps &#124; |work=MLB.com|date=May 23, 2014 |accessdate=June 3, 2014}}</ref>

